---
/**
 * @file DocsOverview.astro
 * @description Overview content listing all mapaPH documentation pages.
 */
---

<span
	class="font-sans text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-mapa-green"
	>Documentation</span
>

<h1
	class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-mapa-green tracking-tight sm:text-5xl font-serif mt-2"
>
	mapaPH Documentation
</h1>

<p class="mt-4 text-lg text-mapa-ink/80 italic leading-relaxed font-serif">
	Guides, data references, and documentation for our open-source tools.
</p>

<!-- SECTION 1: Applications Directory -->
<div class="mt-10 border-t border-mapa-contour/60 pt-8 flex flex-col gap-10">
	<div>
		<h2
			class="text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-6 border-b border-mapa-contour/40 pb-2"
		>
			Applications Directory
		</h2>

		<div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
			<!-- Lens -->
			<div>
				<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif">
						<a
							href="/docs/lens"
							class="hover:text-mapa-green transition-colors duration-200"
						>
							Lens
						</a>
					</h3>
					<span
						class="font-sans text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider bg-mapa-green/10 text-mapa-green px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded"
					>
						Active
					</span>
				</div>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed">
					User guide and documentation for Lens, our interactive map
					viewer and GeoJSON export utility for Philippine
					administrative divisions.
				</p>
				<a
					href="/docs/lens"
					class="font-sans text-xs font-semibold text-mapa-green hover:underline mt-2 inline-block"
				>
					Read Guide &rarr;
				</a>
			</div>

			<!-- To-Cubao -->
			<div class="border-t border-mapa-contour/30 pt-6">
				<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-mapa-ink/60 font-serif">
						<a
							href="/docs/to-cubao"
							class="hover:text-mapa-green transition-colors duration-200"
						>
							To-Cubao
						</a>
					</h3>
					<span
						class="font-sans text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider bg-mapa-clay/20 text-mapa-clay px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded"
					>
						In Development
					</span>
				</div>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/70 leading-relaxed">
					Documentation for our proposed transit routing and terminal
					locator tool for the Cubao hub.
				</p>
				<a
					href="/docs/to-cubao"
					class="font-sans text-xs font-semibold text-mapa-green hover:underline mt-2 inline-block"
				>
					View Project Status &rarr;
				</a>
			</div>

			<!-- Compaws -->
			<div class="border-t border-mapa-contour/30 pt-6">
				<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-mapa-ink/60 font-serif">
						<a
							href="/docs/compaws"
							class="hover:text-mapa-green transition-colors duration-200"
						>
							Compaws
						</a>
					</h3>
					<span
						class="font-sans text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider bg-mapa-clay/20 text-mapa-clay px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded"
					>
						In Development
					</span>
				</div>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/70 leading-relaxed">
					Documentation for our proposed directory mapping
					animal-welcoming parks, cafes, and establishments.
				</p>
				<a
					href="/docs/compaws"
					class="font-sans text-xs font-semibold text-mapa-green hover:underline mt-2 inline-block"
				>
					View Project Status &rarr;
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 2: Getting Started -->
<div class="mt-12 border-t border-mapa-contour/60 pt-8">
	<h2
		class="text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-6 border-b border-mapa-contour/40 pb-2"
	>
		Getting Started with the Tools
	</h2>
	<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
		If you are new to the mapaPH ecosystem, we recommend starting with the
		following core steps to explore geographic and census data:
	</p>
	<ol class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 list-decimal pl-5 space-y-4">
		<li>
			<strong>Access the Viewer:</strong> Launch the <a
				href="https://lens.mapaph.com"
				target="_blank"
				rel="noopener noreferrer"
				class="text-mapa-green hover:underline font-semibold"
				>Lens Web Application</a
			> to view the interactive map canvas.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Select Administrative Levels:</strong> Use the left-side control
			panel to switch the boundary outlines between Regional, Provincial, Municipal/City,
			and Barangay subdivisions.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Apply Data Overlays:</strong> Toggle the map layers to overlay
			visual demographics (PSA population stats), local government financial
			assets, or election histories.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Export Boundaries:</strong> Click on any administrative section
			and choose the export option to download a local, standards-compliant
			GeoJSON file containing boundary coordinate data.
		</li>
	</ol>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 3: Administrative Geography Glossary -->
<div class="mt-12 border-t border-mapa-contour/60 pt-8">
	<h2
		class="text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-6 border-b border-mapa-contour/40 pb-2"
	>
		Philippine Administrative Geography Glossary
	</h2>
	<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
		Our tools and datasets utilize standard administrative classifications
		defined by the Philippine government. Understanding these terms helps
		when querying datasets:
	</p>
	<dl class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 space-y-6">
		<div>
			<dt class="font-serif font-bold text-base text-mapa-green">
				Region (Rehiyon)
			</dt>
			<dd
				class="mt-1 leading-relaxed pl-4 border-l-2 border-mapa-contour"
			>
				The primary administrative grouping used to organize the
				provinces of the Philippines for planning purposes (e.g., NCR,
				CALABARZON, Region VI). Regions do not possess separate local
				government corporate powers.
			</dd>
		</div>
		<div>
			<dt class="font-serif font-bold text-base text-mapa-green">
				Province (Probinsya)
			</dt>
			<dd
				class="mt-1 leading-relaxed pl-4 border-l-2 border-mapa-contour"
			>
				A primary political subdivision consisting of component cities
				and municipalities. Governed by a provincial board and governor.
			</dd>
		</div>
		<div>
			<dt class="font-serif font-bold text-base text-mapa-green">
				City or Municipality (Lungsod o Bayan)
			</dt>
			<dd
				class="mt-1 leading-relaxed pl-4 border-l-2 border-mapa-contour"
			>
				Local Government Units (LGUs) composed of barangays.
				Municipalities are classified by income, while cities may be
				Component Cities (under a province) or Highly Urbanized Cities
				(independent of provinces).
			</dd>
		</div>
		<div>
			<dt class="font-serif font-bold text-base text-mapa-green">
				Barangay
			</dt>
			<dd
				class="mt-1 leading-relaxed pl-4 border-l-2 border-mapa-contour"
			>
				The smallest administrative division and primary political unit
				in the Philippines. Serves as the primary planning and
				implementing body of government policies and community
				activities.
			</dd>
		</div>
		<div>
			<dt class="font-serif font-bold text-base text-mapa-green">
				PSGC (Philippine Standard Geographic Code)
			</dt>
			<dd
				class="mt-1 leading-relaxed pl-4 border-l-2 border-mapa-contour"
			>
				A unique 9-digit (expandable to 10-digit) classification code
				assigned by the Philippine Statistics Authority (PSA) to
				systematically identify regions, provinces, municipalities, and
				barangays. Crucial for structured data matching.
			</dd>
		</div>
	</dl>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 4: Developer Integration Example -->
<div class="mt-12 border-t border-mapa-contour/60 pt-8">
	<h2
		class="text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-6 border-b border-mapa-contour/40 pb-2"
	>
		Developer Integration Example
	</h2>
	<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
		The data generated by our tools can be accessed programmatically. Here
		is a sample JavaScript example demonstrating how to fetch and parse
		municipality boundary GeoJSON files:
	</p>

	<pre
		class="bg-mapa-canvas-dark border border-mapa-contour/80 rounded p-4 text-xs font-mono overflow-x-auto text-mapa-ink leading-relaxed">{`// Example: Fetch a specific municipality's boundary data via PSGC key
const psgcCode = "045618000"; // Example PSGC code for a municipality
const geojsonUrl = \`https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Shiiroi/mapaph/main/public/data/municipalities/\${psgcCode}.geojson\`;

async function fetchBoundaryData() {
  try {
    const response = await fetch(geojsonUrl);
    if (!response.ok) {
      throw new Error(\`HTTP error! Status: \${response.status}\`);
    }
    const boundary = await response.json();
    
    console.log("Boundary Name:", boundary.properties.name);
    console.log("Geography Type:", boundary.geometry.type);
    console.log("Coordinates count:", boundary.geometry.coordinates[0].length);
    
    return boundary;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Failed to retrieve geographic coordinate data:", error);
  }
}`}</pre>
</div>
